# helper function
def categorical_inspection(df, target, variable):
    print ('The Variable is:', variable)
    print ('-'*50)
    counts = df[variable].value_counts()
    if counts.count() <= 500:
        print ('Frequency Statistics: ')
        print (counts.sort_index())
        print ('-'*50)
        
        print ('Bar Chart: ')
        plt.figure(figsize=(20,16))
        counter=Counter(df[variable])
        sns.barplot(list(counter.keys()), list(counter.values()))
        plt.xlabel(variable)
        plt.ylabel('Number')
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        print ('-'*50)
        
        plt.figure(figsize=(30,20))
        sns.countplot(x=variable, hue=target, data=df)
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.show()
    else:
        print ('More than 50 Categories!')
    print ('='*50)
    
def numeric_inspection(df, target, variable):
    print ('Variable Name:', variable)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
    plt.hist(df[df[target]==1][variable], bins=10, label='v=1', alpha=0.5)
    plt.hist(df[df[target]==0][variable], bins=10, label='v=0', alpha=0.5)
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
    print ('='*50)

In [29]:
description = []
missing_count = 0

for i in dataset['description']:
    try:
        description.append(len(i))
    except TypeError:
        missing_count += 1

plt.hist(description, bins=100, range=[0, 2000])
plt.gca().set(title='Description Frequency', ylabel='Frequency', xlabel='Length')
plt.show()
plt.close()

print('Total #', len(dataset['description']))
print('# missing:', missing_count)
print('# not missing:', len(description))

Total # 17880
# missing: 1
# not missing: 17879
